\id 1CH Matupi Chin Standard Bible 
\h 1KHOKHUEN 
\toc1 1 KHOKHUEN 
\toc2 1Khokhuen 
\toc3 1Kh 
\mt1 KHOKHUEN CABU  
\mt3 A Pacuek Nah  
\mt4 (The First Book of the Chronicles)  
\is1 Khokhuen Cabu A Pacuek Kawng  
\im Khokhuen Cabu a pacuek neh a pabae he lamhma ah pakhat lam ni a om. Adam lamkah a tong tih 538 \sc b.c.\sc* Babylon vangsawn lamkah a mael uh hil kah Pathen pilnam kah khokhuen cil a rhui te a thuep. He cabu aka daek kung he mingpha pawt dae, Hebru olkah a hnonah ngawn bahoeng khuet, a tloe tloe kah cil ol te pakhat la a cului. \k Samuel I, II, Manghai I, II\k* dongkah pakhat la a cului thai. Manghai David neh Manghai Solomon kawng he anah la a thui tih, bawknah hmuen khaw Jerusalem te a kungsut. He cabu loh olpuei la a thui tah, a tue he lang tih thovael mai cakhaw Pathen tah a pilnam taengah uepom la om. Uepom hlang te a bom te a tueng sak. Khokhuen Cabu a pacuek dongah Israel ca te vangsawn ah tamna la kum 70 om dae amah kho neh tukkainah a khueh uh yoeyah te a tael. Aboel pakhat lamloh parhet hil te Adam lamloh a rhuirhong kawng a tael. Aboel pako dongah tah Babylon lamkah aka mael rhoek kawng a tael. A tloe dongah tah Manghai David kah a kawng, a thaomnah, a boeimangnah a tael. A hnukhueng te David a dueknah neh Solomon Manghaila a tueknah kawng a thui. \k Khokhuen Cabu I & II\k* he 400 \sc b.c\sc* tluk vaengah a tael.  
\iot Sawt Yoeinah  
\io1 Adam Lamloh Babylon tamna la a om hil \ior 1.1—9.34\ior*  
\io1 David Bawkim tongkung \ior 9.35—29.30\ior*  
